.TH "BI2CF" 6 "Jan 30 2003" "" ""
.SH NAME
bi2cf \- a map conversion tool for Crimson Fields
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.ad l
.hy 0
.HP 6
\fBbi2cf\fR \fImapname\fR [\-p\ 1|2] [\-f\ b|1|2|h] [\-l] [\-t\ \fImapname\fR] [\-i\ \fImapinfo\fR] [\-o\ \fIoutfile\fR] [\-d\ \fImapdir\fR] [\-O\ \fIdestdir\fR] [\-q]
.ad
.hy
.ad l
.hy 0
.HP 6
\fBbi2cf\fR {\fB\-h\fR | \fB\-v\fR}
.ad
.hy

.SH "DESCRIPTION"

.PP
\fBbi2cf\fR is a map conversion tool for Crimson Fields\&. It takes the data files of maps from Battle Isle, Battle Isle Data Disk 1 or 2, or History Line 1914\-1918 and converts them into map sources usable with the \fBcfed\fR(6) map compiler for Crimson Fields\&. \fBbi2cf\fR can handle both uncompressed maps and levels crunched with TPWM\&.

.PP
For some units and tiles there are no corresponding counterparts in Crimson Fields\&. These cases are mapped to similar ones if available\&. As a result some maps will not be as balanced as the originals, others may be unwinnable, and still others may even fail to compile\&. If this happens the map in question needs to be adjusted manually\&.

.SH "OPTIONS"

.TP
\fB\-d\fR \fImapdir\fR
Set the location of the Battle Isle map files\&.

.TP
\fB\-f\fR b|1|2|h
Force map type to Battle Isle / BI Data Disk 1 / BI Data Disk 2 / History Line, respectively\&. Use this option when map format autodetection does not work correctly\&. Maps from BI Data Disk 1 will always be detected as standard Battle Isle maps, so you have to use \fB\-f 1\fR in that case\&.

.TP
\fB\-h\fR
Print a usage message on standard output and exit\&.

.TP
\fB\-i\fR \fImapinfo\fR
Set map info message\&.

.TP
\fB\-l\fR
Skip last row and column of the map\&. This is necessary for maps from the PC version of Battle Isle\&.

.TP
\fB\-o\fR \fIoutfile\fR
Write map to file \fIoutfile\fR\&. Default file name is \fImapname\&.src\fR\&.

.TP
\fB\-O\fR \fIdestdir\fR
Set target directory for the converted map\&. This setting is ignored if a map name was given using the \fB\-t\fR option\&.

.TP
\fB\-p\fR 1|2
Set default number of players for this map\&.

.TP
\fB\-q\fR
Run quietly\&. Don't print processing information on standard output\&.

.TP
\fB\-t\fR \fImapname\fR
Set title and file name for the converted map\&. Default is \fImaptype\-mapname\fR\&.

.TP
\fB\-v\fR
Print version information on standard output and exit\&.

